headline: Starbucks Cafe Sales Stabilize After Year-and-a-Half-Long Slide
summary: Starbucks  said its turnaround efforts are stabilizing the world’s largest coffee chain.  The Seattle company on Wednesday reported the U.S. same-store sales for the three months ended Sept. 28 were flat, an improvement after six consecutive quarterly declines.  For its fourth quarter, Starbucks reported earnings adjusted for one-time items of 52 cents a share, missing the 56-cent estimate from analysts polled by FactSet.

headline: Starbucks (NASDAQ:SBUX) Surprises With Q3 Sales
summary: Coffeehouse chain Starbucks (NASDAQ:SBUX) reported Q3 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 5.5% year on year to $9.57 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.52 per share was 6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.A previous version of this article incorrectly stated that the company had 18,311 locations at the end of the quarter. This has been updated to reflect the correct count (40,990).

headline: Starbucks halts 2-year sales slide, but costly improvements hurt its profits
summary: Starbucks halted a long sales slide in its fiscal fourth quarter as pumpkin drinks and improved service brought customers back to its stores.  Starbucks Chairman and CEO Brian Niccol said the results indicate the company's turnaround, which he put in place after joining Starbucks a little more than a year ago, is working.  Niccol has set new hospitality standards, redesigned stores to be cozier and more welcoming and adjusted staffing levels to better handle peak hours.
